  "prompt": "Why is Quora blocking my name saying it doesn't conform?",
  "response": "Quora may block or reject your name if it doesn't conform to their **Community Guidelines** or **Name Policy**. Here are some common reasons why this might happen:\n\n### 1. **Use of Symbols, Numbers, or Unusual Characters**  \n   Quora requires names to be written in standard alphabetic characters. If your name includes symbols, numbers, or excessive special characters, it may be flagged.\n\n### 2. **Name Appears Fake or Inappropriate**  \n   If your name seems fabricated, humorous, or offensive, Quora may block it. Names that impersonate others or resemble well-known figures (e.g., \"Elon Musk Jr.\") are also likely to be rejected.\n\n### 3. **Use of Titles or Honorifics**  \n   Quora discourages including titles like \"Dr.,\" \"Professor,\" or \"Queen\" in your name unless they are part of your legal name or you\u2019ve verified them.\n\n### 4. **Incomplete or Too Short Names**  \n   Names that are too short (e.g., \"A\") or incomplete (e.g., \"John D.\") may not meet Quora\u2019s standards.\n\n### 5. **Violation of Quora\u2019s Authenticity Policy**  \n   Quora requires users to use their real, full names (or a commonly used nickname). If your name doesn\u2019t align with this policy, it may be blocked.\n\n### 6. **Potential Impersonation**  \n   If your name is similar to another user\u2019s or a public figure\u2019s, Quora may block it to prevent confusion or impersonation.\n\n### What You Can Do:  \n- **Use your real, full name** or a commonly used nickname.  \n- Avoid symbols, numbers, or unnecessary characters.  \n- If you believe your name was blocked unfairly, you can **appeal to Quora\u2019s support team** by contacting them through their Help Center.\n\nMake sure to review Quora\u2019s [Name Policy](https://www.quora.com/help/user_profiles) for specific guidelines.",
